<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1135" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1135">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01B11/12–1644</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-16">December 16, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Soviet Ambassador called upon me this morning at his request.</p>
                        <p>He stated that it had been three weeks since he had raised with me the
                            question of the alleged deserter, Mr. Kravchenko, and that he was <pb facs="1250" n="1240" xml:id="pg_1240"/> extremely anxious to have a
                            reply. He said he attached the greatest importance to the matter.</p>
                        <p>I told the Ambassador that the whole situation was being studied and that
                            I would communicate with him promptly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>